### Phase 1: Building a Custom Widget (The Foundation)
Our first goal is to create an independent building block

Task:
- [ ] Create a new file named "Tlacitko.py".
- [ ] Set up the "Tlacitko" class inheriting from "QWidget".
- [ ] Initialize the parent class using "super().__init__()".
- [ ] Create the UI elements: One "QLineEdit" (for the number) and three "QPushButton"s (+, -, and Color).
- [ ] Arrange the layout: Put the three buttons in a "QVBoxLayout" (vertical column).
- [ ] Create a main "QHBoxLayout" (horizontal) and divide the space: 70% for the text field, 30% for the vertical button layout.
- [ ] Apply the main layout to the widget using "self.setLayout()".
